ilogy. I would see Metroids as scary and hungry enemies of Samus Aran that threaten the galaxy. I would also like it mature-rated, but not to the extent of the Dead Space series. Additionally, I\'d prefer if the main antagonist of the reboot were a corrupt CO instead of a fire breathing dragon called Ridley or a Godzilla-esque beast with spikes on its belly and three eyes!</div><div><br></div><div>It seems like Nintendo is squandering their canonical resources in the Metroid franchise. That\'s how the idea came in my head. Star Fox could use a reboot, too. Won\'t be the first time, but there\'s a Wii U game of Star Fox. Hope it\'s worth to check out.</div>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"html\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:4:{s:3:\"rel\";s:7:\"replies\";s:4:\"type\";s:20:\"application/atom+xml\";s:4:\"href\";s:72:\"http://miletich2.blogspot.com/feeds/3091863920631975731/comments/default\";s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"Post Comments\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:4:{s:3:\"rel\";s:7:\"replies\";s:4:\"type\";s:9:\"text/html\";s:4:\"href\";s:86:\"http://www.blogger.com/comment.g?blogID=3424051896540341526&postID=3091863920631975731\";s:5:\"title\";s:10:\"0 Comments\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"edit\";s:4:\"type\";s:20:\"application/atom+xml\";s:4:\"href\";s:82:\"http://www.blogger.com/feeds/3424051896540341526/posts/default/3091863920631975731\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:20:\"application/atom+xml\"