:7:{s:2:\"id\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-3424051896540341526.post-301550235528065958\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:9:\"published\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"2014-06-14T14:43:00.000-07:00\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"updated\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"2014-06-16T14:27:32.661-07:00\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"Love my job\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"text\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"content\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:2666:\"It can be tedious as watching the grass grow millimeter by millimeter. But damn it! It\'s my means of making money, making friends and also serving customers to the limit. It\'s an experience I shan\'t forget because as long as I\'ve been living at home without school or work, especially in the hot summertime, life was just empty. I work at a thrift store in Lafayette, CA. I have a beautiful job coach, a fairly stern manager, a flexible transit system and a few companions who run the register. This is my idea of living the American dream!<div><br></div><div>Now, the concept itself doesn\'t have to be, nor can it be, all opulent or free of difficulty. Otherwise, you\'re in a world of emptiness. I&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: \'Helvetica Neue Light\', HelveticaNeue-Light, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">have goals such as renting my own apartment. But it can\'t be rushed since the housing department is corrupt around here.</span></div><div><span style=\"font-family: \'Helvetica Neue Light\', HelveticaNeue-Light, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\"><br></span></div><div><span style=\"font-family: \'Helvetica Neue Light\', HelveticaNeue-Light, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\">There are others who feel they no longer embrace the American dream because they relentlessly blame President Obama and his healthcare law, Obamacare. While I see Obama as a godsend who helps the poor and those hurt by climate change, others feel harm during his presidency. Fortunately for the Obama administration, my job isn\'t in jeopardy as some in Texas, North Carolina and in other non-democratic states are.</span></div><div><span style=\"font-family: \'Helvetica Neue Light\', HelveticaNeue-Light, helvetica, arial, sans-serif;\"><br></span></div><div><font face=\"Helvetica Neue Light, HelveticaNeue-Light, helvetica, arial, sans-serif\">I still loathe George W. Bush, but a lot of people are starting to like him now because he\'s either out of office or Obama is doing more harm to this country than the former was! So much harm several Americans are now crying for the president\'s impeachment. Midterm elections are coming this November and I\'m not gonna lie to you my friends. I don\'t care if the republicans or democrats win the midterm elections. If there is any political party who I feel should rule America more than elephants or donkeys, it\'s either a libertarian or independent party. I wish for a government with narrower tax brackets, proper immigration control and a revised second amendment that grants citizens access to control if, and only if, they\'ve been constantly victimized by potential terrorists, radical gangs or absolute left-wing or absolute right-wing.</font></div>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:4:\"type\";s:4:\"html\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:4:{s:3:\"rel\";s:7:\"replies\";s:4:\"type\";s:20:\"application/atom+xml\";s:4:\"href\";s:71:\"http://miletich2.blogspot.com/feeds/301550235528065958/comments/default\";s:5:\"title\";s:13:\"Post Commen