cit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"WonderPlugin Audio Player Plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"WordPress Carousel Plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/?p=3288\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:414:\"Product WonderPlugin Carousel This tutorial will show you how to add a recent post carousel or a category post carousel to your website. You will find how easy it is to automatically update your carousel using WonderPlugin Carousel. Step1. Prepare &#8230; <a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-tutorials/how-to-create-a-wordpress-post-carousel/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"WonderPlugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10906:\"<p><strong>Product</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-carousel/\" target=\"_blank\">WonderPlugin Carousel</a></p>\n<p>This tutorial will show you how to add a recent post carousel or a category post carousel to your website. You will find how easy it is to automatically update your carousel using WonderPlugin Carousel.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-3288\"></span></p>\n<div style=\"width:560px;height:315px;max-width:100%;margin:24px auto;\">\n<iframe width=\"100%\" height=\"100%\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/j32YM7UvvGk\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen></iframe>\n</div>\n<p><strong>Step1. Prepare the post with specific configuration</strong></p>\n<p>1.	In the post editor, click the Screen Options tab on the top right,  make sure you tick the boxes of Categories, Featured Image and Excerpt<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-screenoption.jpg\" class=\"wplightbox\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-3325\"><img src=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-screenoption-600x184.jpg\" alt=\"wordpress-post-carousel-screenoption\" width=\"600\" height=\"184\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3325\" srcset=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-screenoption-600x184.jpg 600w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-screenoption-240x74.jpg 240w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-screenoption-500x153.jpg 500w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-screenoption.jpg 756w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p>2.	Choose the categories. You can select one or more categories. The category is one of the filter selections when you create the post carousel.</p>\n<p>3.	Set the featured image. The featured image will be added to the carousel as the post image. </p>\n<p>4.	Fill in the excerpt filed. The excerpts are optional summaries of your post content that can be used as the description of the carousel item.<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-excerpt.jpg\" class=\"wplightbox\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-3321\"><img src=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-excerpt-600x402.jpg\" alt=\"wordpress-post-carousel-excerpt\" width=\"600\" height=\"402\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3321\" srcset=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-excerpt-600x402.jpg 600w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-excerpt-240x161.jpg 240w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-excerpt-768x515.jpg 768w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-excerpt-448x300.jpg 448w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-excerpt.jpg 840w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p><strong>Step2 create the post carousel</strong></p>\n<p>1.	Move your mouse to the WonderPlugin Carousel under the dashboard on the left side of your page. This will show you options for your carousel. Choose “New Carousel\".<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-new-carousel.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-3323\"><img src=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-new-carousel-600x333.jpg\" class=\"wplightbox\" alt=\"wordpress-post-carousel-new-carousel\" width=\"600\" height=\"333\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3323\" srcset=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-new-carousel-600x333.jpg 600w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-new-carousel-240x133.jpg 240w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-new-carousel-500x278.jpg 500w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-new-carousel.jpg 666w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p>2.	In the “New Carousel” page, at step1 “Images & Videos”, click “Add WordPress Posts” tab.<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-new.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-3322\"><img src=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-new-600x264.jpg\" class=\"wplightbox\" alt=\"wordpress-post-carousel-new\" width=\"600\" height=\"264\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3322\" srcset=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-new-600x264.jpg 600w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-new-240x106.jpg 240w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-new-500x220.jpg 500w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-new.jpg 740w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p>3.	Click the drop-down menu of “Select Posts”. Then choose the item from “Recent Post” or “Category”. If you choose “Recent Post”, the carousel will display all of the recent posts up to the number you set. If you choose “Category”, the carousel will only display the posts which are belonging to the category you select. Click OK button.<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-add-post.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-3318\"><img src=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-add-post-600x378.jpg\" class=\"wplightbox\" alt=\"wordpress-post-carousel-add-post\" width=\"600\" height=\"378\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3318\" srcset=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-add-post-600x378.jpg 600w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-add-post-240x151.jpg 240w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-add-post-768x484.jpg 768w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-add-post-476x300.jpg 476w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-add-post.jpg 817w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p>4.	In the “New Carousel” page, click the step2 “Skins” tab, choose the skins you like. Only some of the skin will display the excerpt as well as the featured image.<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-skins.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-3326\"><img src=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-skins-600x310.jpg\" class=\"wplightbox\" alt=\"wordpress-post-carousel-skins\" width=\"600\" height=\"310\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3326\" srcset=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-skins-600x310.jpg 600w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-skins-240x124.jpg 240w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-skins-768x397.jpg 768w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-skins-500x259.jpg 500w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-skins.jpg 980w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p>5.	Click “Save & Publish” button. You can click “View Carousel” to preview the carousel. If you are not satisfied with the one you just created, click “Edit Carousel “, this will take you to the “Edit Carousel” page. Then repeat step 3 and 4.  If you are happy with the carousel, you only need to copy the shortcode or php code.<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/wordpress-post-carousel-copy-code.jpg\" class=\"wplightbox\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-3328\"><img src=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/wordpress-post-carousel-copy-code-600x92.jpg\" alt=\"wordpress-post-carousel-copy-code\" width=\"600\" height=\"92\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3328\" srcset=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/wordpress-post-carousel-copy-code-600x92.jpg 600w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/wordpress-post-carousel-copy-code-240x37.jpg 240w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/wordpress-post-carousel-copy-code-768x118.jpg 768w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/wordpress-post-carousel-copy-code-1024x157.jpg 1024w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/wordpress-post-carousel-copy-code-500x77.jpg 500w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/wordpress-post-carousel-copy-code.jpg 1026w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p>6.	Open the page or post you want to insert the post carousel, paste the code in the “Text” window. Then click the “Publish” or “Update” button on the right side of the page.<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-paste-code.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-3324\"><img src=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-paste-code-600x343.jpg\" class=\"wplightbox\" alt=\"wordpress-post-carousel-paste-code\" width=\"600\" height=\"343\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3324\" srcset=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-paste-code-600x343.jpg 600w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-paste-code-240x137.jpg 240w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-paste-code-500x286.jpg 500w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-paste-code.jpg 685w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a><br />\nNow you got a post carousel which could be automatically updated when you post new contents.<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-3317\"><img src=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-600x357.jpg\" class=\"wplightbox\" alt=\"wordpress-post-carousel\" width=\"600\" height=\"357\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-3317\" srcset=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-600x357.jpg 600w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-240x143.jpg 240w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel-500x298.jpg 500w, https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/wordpress-post-carousel.jpg 677w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a> </p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:39:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:6:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:40:\"Different sliders for desktop and mobile\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:98:\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/responsive-wordpress-slider/different-sliders-for-mobile-and-desktop/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 23 Feb 2016 03:35:05 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27:\"Responsive WordPress Slider\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"WordPress Slider\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23:\"WordPress Slider Plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/?p=3281\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:418:\"Product WonderPlugin Slider Question Some of our pages function better with different skins depending on whether we are using desktop or mobile. Is there a way to use different skins for desktop and mobile? Answer You can create two WordPress &#8230; <a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/responsive-wordpress-slider/different-sliders-for-mobile-and-desktop/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"WonderPlugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1290:\"<p><strong>Product</strong></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-slider/\" target=\"_blank\">WonderPlugin Slider</a></p>\n<p><strong>Question</strong></p>\n<p>Some of our pages function better with different skins depending on whether we are using desktop or mobile.</p>\n<p>Is there a way to use different skins for desktop and mobile?</p>\n<p><strong>Answer</strong></p>\n<p>You can create two WordPress sliders, one for mobile, one for desktop.</p>\n<p>After you have created two sliders, you can add the following code to your post or page. Please be sure to change the ID value in the code to that of your own sliders.</p>\n<pre class=\"brush: xml; title: ; notranslate\">\r\n&lt;div id=&quot;largescreen&quot;&gt;\r\n[wonderplugin_slider id=&quot;1&quot;]\r\n&lt;/div&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;div id=&quot;smallscreen&quot;&gt;\r\n[wonderplugin_slider id=&quot;2&quot;]\r\n&lt;/div&gt;\r\n</pre>\n<p>Then you can add the following CSS code to your WordPress theme style.css file to show the small slider when the screen width is less than 640px:</p>\n<pre class=\"brush: css; title: ; notranslate\">\r\n#largescreen {\r\n  display: block;\r\n}\r\n\r\n#smallscreen {\r\n  display: none;\r\n}\r\n\r\n@media (max-width: 640px) {\r\n  #largescreen {\r\n    display: none;\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  #smallscreen {\r\n    display: block;\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n</pre>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:44:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n	\n\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:3:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"How to add a poster image for HTML5 video lightbox?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:105:\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-video-lightbox/how-to-add-a-poster-image-for-html5-video-lightbox/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 16 Feb 2016 04:55:35 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"WordPress Lightbox\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"WordPress Lightbox Plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24:\"WordPress Video Lightbox\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22:\"WordPress Video Player\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:36:\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/?p=3248\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:427:\"Product: WonderPlugin Lightbox Question: I wonder how can I add a poster image for HTML5 video lightbox? Answer: The HTML5 poster image feature is available in WonderPlugin Lightbox version 4.0 and above. If you are using an old version, please &#8230; <a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-video-lightbox/how-to-add-a-poster-image-for-html5-video-lightbox/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&#8594;</span></a>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:9:\"enclosure\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"url\";s:92:\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/plugins/wonderplugin-lightbox/images/demo-video0.mp4\";s:6:\"length\";s:6:\"302611\";s:4:\"type\";s:9:\"video/mp4\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"url\";s:93:\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/plugins/wonderplugin-lightbox/images/demo-video0.webm\";s:6:\"length\";s:6:\"386398\";s:4:\"type\";s:10:\"video/webm\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"WonderPlugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1600:\"<p><strong>Product</strong>:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wordpress-lightbox/\" target=\"_blank\">WonderPlugin Lightbox</a></p>\n<p><strong>Question</strong>:</p>\n<p>I wonder how can I add a poster image for HTML5 video lightbox?</p>\n<p><strong>Answer</strong>:</p>\n<p>The HTML5 poster image feature is available in WonderPlugin Lightbox version 4.0 and above. If you are using an old version, please upgrade your plugin first.</p>\n<p>In the plugin, Lightbox Options menu, there is an option \"Video poster image (absolute URL)\", you can use the option to specify a poster image for all HTML5 videos.</p>\n<p>Or you can use a data tag <span style=\"color:#ff0000;\">data-html5videoposter</span> to specify a poster image for the lightbox link, for example:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/plugins/wonderplugin-lightbox/images/demo-video0.mp4\" class=\"wplightbox\" data-webm=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/plugins/wonderplugin-lightbox/images/demo-video0.webm\" data-html5videoposter=\"https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/gallery.jpg\">Video Lightbox</a></p>\n<p>The HTML code is as following:</p>\n<pre class=\"brush: xml; title: ; notranslate\">\r\n&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/plugins/wonderplugin-lightbox/images/demo-video0.mp4&quot; class=&quot;wplightbox&quot; data-webm=&quot;https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/plugins/wonderplugin-lightbox/images/demo-video0.webm&quot; data-html5videoposter=&quot;https://www.wonderplugin.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/gallery.jpg&quot;&gt;Video Lightbox&lt;/a&gt;\r\n</pre>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:4:\"href\";s:34: