tices emergent curriculum. She has studied theater and improv at A.C.T. in San Francisco as well as graduated from The Second City Training Center in Hollywood where she studied improv and sketch comedy. She has her Bachelors Degree in Early Childhood Education. Her focus is on inclusive classrooms where curriculum is designed to allow children and young adults to feel comfortable expressing themselves in whichever way they feel most comfortable. She believes when we can share with one another what has been taught then, and only then, are we actually learning.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;/div&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;div class=\"row april-bio\"&gt;\r\n&lt;img src=\"/wp-content/themes/creativeforces/images/april.jpg\" id=\"april-pic\" class=\"col-md-6 about-us-pics\" alt=\"\"&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=\"col-md-6 about-us-text\"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Maja Miletich&lt;/strong&gt; is the CEO of &lt;a href=\"\"&gt;Zip Zap Zop&lt;/a&gt; Kids, LLC. She has worked with children on many levels. Having a brother with Autism has given her an understanding of how powerful communication is for ALL children. She has worked for years as a teacher where she practices emergent curriculum. She has studied theater and improv at A.C.T. in San Francisco as well as graduated from The Second City Training Center in Hollywood where she studied improv and sketch comedy. She has her Bachelors Degree in Early Childhood Education. Her focus is on inclusive classrooms where curriculum is designed to allow children and young adults to feel comfortable expressing themselves in whichever way they feel most comfortable. She believes when we can share with one another what has been taught then, and only then, are we actually learning.&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;/div&gt;\r\n&lt;/div&gt;\r\n\r\n&lt;h4 class=\"text-center\"&gt;Members of the Board&lt;/h4&gt;\r\n&lt;div class=\"row\"&gt;\r\n&lt;div class=\"col-md-4\"&gt;&lt;div class=\"text-center\"&gt;&lt;img src=\"/wp-content/themes/creativeforces/images/ari.jpg\" class=\"members-board-pics\" 